                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-35-victim362 t18200412-35-viclabel193"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200412-35-victim364 t18200412-35-viclabel193"></join> there - Mr. David lives in the house with his family, and Mr. William lives at the other shop in the Borough. On the 5th of April, between ten and eleven o'clock at night, I was shutting up the shop, and saw the prisoner come out with this sheeting under his arm. I ran in, spoke to Mason, then followed the prisoner, and caught him in Middle-row, with the sheeting under his arm; the watchman took it from him. He said he was not the person that took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200412-35-person368">
                  HENRY 
                  MASON
               <interp inst="t18200412-35-person368" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
